      <section eId="sec_CC-2818">
        <num>CC 2818</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="CC-2818__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A partner ceases to be a member of a partnership upon: his death or interdiction; his being granted an order for relief under Chapter 7 or confirmation of a plan of liquidation or the appointment of a trustee of his estate under Chapter 11 of the Bankruptcy Code; his interest in the partnership being seized and not released as provided in Article 2819; his expulsion from the partnership; or his withdrawal from the partnership.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-2818__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A partner also ceases to be a member of a partnership in accordance with the provisions of the contract of partnership.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109888</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
